1️⃣ Core Teaching (Simple, Exam-Oriented)
🔹 Who is the Governor?

The Governor is:

Head of the State
Representative of the President
Part of State Executive

📌 Mentioned in Articles 153–162

🔵 Appointment of Governor
Appointed by the President
Not elected

📌 Acts as agent of the Centre in the State.

🔹 Qualifications
Citizen of India
Minimum age: 35 years
🔴 Term
Normally 5 years
Holds office during pleasure of President

📌 Can be removed anytime.

🔹 Powers of Governor
1️⃣ Executive Powers
Appoints Chief Minister
Appoints Council of Ministers
Appoints Advocate General
2️⃣ Legislative Powers
Summons State Legislature
Assents to bills
Can reserve bill for President
3️⃣ Financial Powers
Budget introduced with Governor’s recommendation
Money Bill needs approval
4️⃣ Judicial Powers
Can grant pardons (state matters)
🔹 Discretionary Powers

Governor can act without advice of Council of Ministers in certain situations:

President’s Rule recommendation
Reserving bills
Appointing CM (hung assembly)

📌 Very important UPSC concept.

🔹 Important Points
Nominal head (real power → Chief Minister)
Link between Centre & State
🔹 Governor vs President
Feature	President	Governor
Level	National	State
Election	Indirect	Appointed
Removal	Impeachment	Pleasure of President
Role	Head of Union	Head of State
